def detect_outliers_iqr(data, column):
    Q1 = data[column].quantile(0.25)
    Q3 = data[column].quantile(0.75)
    IQR = Q3 - Q1
    lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
    upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR

    outliers = data[(data[column] < lower_bound) | (data[column] > upper_bound)]

    return outliers

outliers_agriculture = detect_outliers_iqr(df, "CO2Emissions_Agriculture")
outliers_transport = detect_outliers_iqr(df, "CO2Emissions_TransportEnergy")
outliers_waste = detect_outliers_iqr(df, "CO2Emissions_Waste")

print("Outliers detected:")
print(f"Agriculture: {len(outliers_agriculture)}")
print(f"Transport: {len(outliers_transport)}")
print(f"Waste: {len(outliers_waste)}")

def detect_outliers_iqr(data, column):
    Q1 = data[column].quantile(0.25)
    Q3 = data[column].quantile(0.75)
    IQR = Q3 - Q1
    lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
    upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR

    outliers = data[(data[column] < lower_bound) | (data[column] > upper_bound)]

    return outliers

outliers_agriculture = detect_outliers_iqr(df_filtered, "CO2Emissions_Agriculture")
outliers_transport = detect_outliers_iqr(df_filtered, "CO2Emissions_TransportEnergy")
outliers_waste = detect_outliers_iqr(df_filtered, "CO2Emissions_Waste")

def detect_outliers_iqr(data, column):
    Q1 = data[column].quantile(0.25)
    Q3 = data[column].quantile(0.75)
    IQR = Q3 - Q1
    lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
    upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR

    outliers = data[(data[column] < lower_bound) | (data[column] > upper_bound)]

    return outliers[["country_name", "region", column]]
